JOHANNESBURG – Fraud-accused Varun Gupta has returned to South Africa from his court-approved trip to India. Gupta's lawyer says he landed back in South Africa on Saturday night. EXCLUSIVE: Ajay Gupta denies being a fugitive Two weeks ago, the Bloemfontein Magistrate's Court granted him permission to attend a religious ceremony in India. The court ordered him to be back by May 27. Varun Gupta is a nephew to the politically-connected Gupta brothers. He has been linked to corruption in the Free State's Estina Dairy Project. eNCA